Distribution. Presently known only from the Aivapui River and Keisalam River (Karnaphuli River drainage), a small stream inside Dampa Tiger Reserve, Mizoram, Northeast India (
Fig. 3
). The Karnaphuli River, locally known as the Khawthlang Tuipui, in Mizoram, is located between the Ganges-Brahmaputra and the Kaladan drainages. Originating from the hills of the Mizoram-Tripura border in India , it flows along the Mizoram- Bangladesh border and then southwest through the Chittagong Hill tract and Chittagong and empties into the Bay of Bengal.
